merican Bandstand era, can work as impediments to progress in the present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAfrican Americans -- Civil rights -- Pennsylvania -- Philadelphia -- History -- 20th century. 0aAfrican AmericansxCivil rightszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aAmerican Bandstand (Television program). 0aCivil rights movements -- Pennsylvania -- Philadelphia -- History -- 20th century. 0aCivil rights movementszPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aMinorities on television. 0aPhiladelphia (Pa.) -- Race relations -- History -- 20th century. 0aSegregation -- Pennsylvania -- Philadelphia -- History -- 20th century. 0aSegregationzPennsylvaniazPhiladelphiaxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / General.2bisacsh  a1950s america.  a1950s us history.  a20th century america.  a20th century entertainment.  aafrican american history.  aamerican bandstand era.  aamerican civil rights movement.  aamerican segregation.  aamerican studies.  ablack history.  abrown vs board of education.  acolor discrimination.  aentertainment and african americans.  aentertainment industry.  ahairspray musical.  ahistory of race and ethnicity.  ahistory of television.  aminority studies.  aphiladelphia civil rights.  asegregation and entertainment.  asegregation and television.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095160040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520951600423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520951600/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles